title: Philippines Employment Rate
description: Employment Rate in Philippines increased to 95 percent in September from 94.70 percent in August of 2022. Employment Rate in Philippines averaged 91.61 percent from 1991 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 95.41 percent in December of 2019 and a record low of 82.40 percent in June of 2020. In Philippines, the employment rate measures the number of people who have a job as a percentage of the labour force. This page provides - Philippines Employment Rate- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Philippine Statistics Authority
